1 Abstract

Summarize the study group, what type of study it is, the main methods and results. This here also serves as an example on how to highlight your text by making a grey box around it. Use the code used above and below this paragraph here. The styling class is defined as boxedtext.

2 Methods

Clinical characteristics were summarized using descriptive statistics. Continuous variables were characterized using median and interquartile range; dichotomous or polytomous variables were characterized using frequencies. Between-group comparisons were evaluated using Wilcoxon rank-sum tests for continuous variables and Fishers exact tests for dichotomous and polytomous variables.

The time to XY was summarized using the Kaplan-Meier curve.

3 Results

In this study, we consider 50 cars. The average speed was 15.4km/h.

Here, table_one() reports mean and standard deviation and median and IQR for continuous variables; frequencies for dichotomous and polytomous variables. In presence of group= arguments, table_one() will perform two sample t-tests (with unequal variance) or Wilcoxon rank-sums tests if there are 2 groups; otherwise ANOVA and Kruskal-Wallis rank sum tests if there are more than 2 groups. The summary for the grouping variable will not included in the grouped table.
